msgid "hero_kicker"
msgstr "CS-Cart · Cloudflare"

msgid "hero_title"
msgstr "Keep Cloudflare settings in a state you can always roll back to"

msgid "hero_subtitle"
msgstr "From CS-Cart admin: keep history and roll back when something breaks. Details below."

msgid "hero_cta_primary"
msgstr "See pricing"

msgid "hero_cta_secondary"
msgstr "See main features"

msgid "problem_section_title"
msgstr "The problem"

msgid "problem_title"
msgstr "One rule change can affect the whole storefront"

msgid "problem_p1"
msgstr "Page Rules and Cache Rules are powerful, but mistakes can hit checkout, APIs, and the admin in one shot."

msgid "problem_p2"
msgstr "Without a fast path back to the last working state, people avoid touching Cloudflare during an outage—and recovery slows down."

msgid "problem_p3"
msgstr "What matters is stable behavior and a way to return to the last working state—not another dashboard that only talks about speed."

msgid "solution_section_title"
msgstr "What this add-on does"

msgid "solution_title"
msgstr "When things break, return to the last working state"

msgid "solution_p1"
msgstr "On Pro, Page Rules and Cache Rules are stored separately, and a new history entry is added only when the live configuration actually changes—so you always have a path back to the last working state."

msgid "solution_p2"
msgstr "During an incident, restore from a saved snapshot instead of guessing which line you changed in the Cloudflare UI."

msgid "pro_disclaimer"
msgstr "Backups, rollback, and applying changes to Cloudflare require Pro. On Free, you can fetch rules and review content locally."

msgid "core_section_title"
msgstr "Main features (Pro)"

msgid "core_title"
msgstr "Backups and rollback"

msgid "core_intro"
msgstr "Built to keep a caching setup that works from being undone by a bad rule—not to chase headline performance metrics."

msgid "core_feature_backup_title"
msgstr "Separate stores per rule type"

msgid "core_feature_backup_desc"
msgstr "Page Rules and Cache Rules are backed up on separate tracks so you can reason about each area."

msgid "core_feature_gen_title"
msgstr "Up to 20 history entries"

msgid "core_feature_gen_desc"
msgstr "Per zone, recent generations are kept within a fixed limit so history does not grow without bound."

msgid "core_feature_snapshot_title"
msgstr "Point-in-time snapshots"

msgid "core_feature_snapshot_desc"
msgstr "Each entry is a snapshot of settings at that moment—compare or restore from it."

msgid "core_feature_fingerprint_title"
msgstr "Detect Cloudflare-side changes and record them"

msgid "core_feature_fingerprint_desc"
msgstr "Fingerprints compare the live zone with the last snapshot and add history only when something actually changed—less noisy drift."

msgid "core_feature_change_title"
msgstr "History grows only on real changes"

msgid "core_feature_change_desc"
msgstr "Because entries appear when the live config diverges from the last save, you spend less time guessing what moved in the dashboard."

msgid "core_feature_rollback_title"
msgstr "Restore the last working state"

msgid "core_feature_rollback_desc"
msgstr "Roll back to the last working snapshot first, then investigate root cause calmly."

msgid "visibility_section_title"
msgstr "Seeing what changed"

msgid "visibility_title"
msgstr "Harder to miss unintended changes"

msgid "visibility_p1"
msgstr "Diffs and history make it easier to follow what changed on Cloudflare—including surprises that are easy to miss if you only stare at the dashboard."

msgid "value_section_title"
msgstr "What we optimize for"

msgid "value_title"
msgstr "Staying up beats vanity metrics"

msgid "value_p1"
msgstr "We care more about fewer outages and fewer panicked hotfixes than about synthetic speed scores—and about not breaking a caching design that already works."

msgid "value_p2"
msgstr "Restore behavior first; you can still dig into root cause afterward."

msgid "design_section_title"
msgstr "Design approach"

msgid "design_title"
msgstr "Guardrails on risky work"

msgid "design_p1"
msgstr "High-impact steps are staged. Snapshots mean you are not forced to trust “whatever shipped last.”"

msgid "design_p2"
msgstr "Even under peak traffic, you can return to a stable configuration before a long postmortem."

